The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Mukesh optimistic 
                                                   Mukesh optimistic 
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Mukesh Kumar feels golf will become Indias second most popular sport after cricket within the next five years.         
	The 44-year old golfer, who believes that the golfing scenario in the country has changed since the Professional Golf Tour of India (PGTI) began initiating tournaments, stressed that more and more golfers would make the game richer and see new talent being identified.         
	Just wait and see, golf will be a major sport after cricket within the next five years. Its gaining in popularity every day, the golfer from Mhow told The Telegraph on Wednesday at the Tollygunge Golf Club.         
	More and more talent will come up and the game will be enriched, he added.         
	According to him, golf these days has become quite competitive. The scenario has changed vastly in the last five years. I feel the PGTI should be given credit for all this. Since they have initiated tournaments we have so many talented golfers around The competition is tough now.         
	Asked about his career plans, Mukesh said: I want to carry on for as long as I am fit. Hope I will be able to carry on until I turn 50 But I want to win every tournament and remain on top, Mukesh said.                                                                                                                       
